1 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 19 O.S. 2021, Section 868.2, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 868.2. The county planning commission shall be composed
4 of seven (7) members to be appointed by the board of county
5 commissioners. One member shall be a member the chair of the board
6 of county commissioners or their designee and the remaining six
7 members shall be residents of the unincorporated areas of the county
8 appointed by the board of county commissioners, with each county
9 commissioner nominating two members. Each such nominee shall reside
10 within the district represented by the county commissioner making
11 the nomination. The term of the chair of the county commissioner
12 member or their designee shall be coextensive with his their term of
13 official office in that position, and all other members shall be
14 appointed for terms of six (6) two (2) years, except that such terms
15 shall be made overlapping and the respective terms of those first
16 appointed may be less than six (6) two (2) years. All members shall
17 serve as such without compensation. Members may be removed by the
18 board of county commissioners for cause after a public hearing held
19 for that purpose and vacancies shall be filled by additional
20 appointments.
21 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 19 O.S. 2021, Section 868.3, is
22 amended to read as follows:
23 Section 868.3. A. The county board of adjustment shall be
24 composed of three (3), five (5), or seven (7) resident property
Req. No. 17579 Page 2

1 owne rs of the county to be appointed by the board of county
2 commissioners. At least one member shall be a resident of the
3 county seat of such county and at least one member shall be duly
4 licensed as an attorney in the State of Oklahoma. Members shall be
5 nominated by the county commissioners in as nearly equal number as
6 practicable, and when the total number of authorized positions
7 cannot be divided equally among the three county commissioners, the
8 remaining nomination or nominations shall be allocated by the board
9 of county commissioners.
10 B. The term of each member shall be three (3) two (2) years
11 except that the terms shall be overlapping and the membership of the
12 board first appointed shall be for terms of one (1), two (2) and
13 three (3) years, respectively respective terms of those first
14 appointed may be less than two (2) years. The board of county
15 commissioners is hereby authorized to fill vacancies which may occur
16 in the board and to appoint a substitute or substitutes to serve in
17 a particular case in which a member or members shall certify his
18 their disqualification. Members may be removed by the board of
19 county commissioners for cause after a public hearing held for that
20 purpose, and vacancies shall be filled by additional appointments.
21 All members of the county board of adjustment shall serve as such
22 without compensation.
23
24
Req. No. 17579 Page 3

1 C. The board of county commissioners may retain private legal
2 counsel to represent and advise the county board of adjustment in
3 the performance of its official duties.
4 D. The county board of adjustment shall elect its own chairman
5 and shall adopt rules of procedure consistent with the provisions of
6 the zoning regulations and the provisions of this act. The
7 chairman, or in his absence the acting chairman, may administer
8 oaths and compel the attendance of witnesses. All hearings of the
9 county board of adjustment shall be open to the public, and minutes
10 shall be kept of all proceedings and official actions, which minutes
11 shall be filed in the office of the board and shall be a public
12 record. The board of adjustment shall fix a reasonable time for the
13 hearing of any appeal and every appeal shall be heard within sixty
14 (60) days from the date of filing.
15 E. Notice of hearings before the county board of adjustment
16 shall be given by at least one (1) publication in a newspaper of
17 general circulation in the county and by mail to the record owners
18 of lands contiguous to the affected area at least fifteen (15) days
19 prior to the date of such hearing.
20 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
21 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 868.23 of Title 19, unless there
22 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
23 On and after the date a county becomes subject to Sections 868.1
24 et seq. of Title 19 of the Oklahoma Statues, all comprehensive
Req. No. 17579 Page 4

1 plan s, master plans, zoning regulations, floodplain regulations,
2 subdivision regulations, resolutions, ordinances, codes, and all
3 amendments, supplements, and modifications thereto, previously
4 adopted or enacted pursuant to any other provision of Section 863.1
5 through Section 869.7 of Title 19 of the Oklahoma Statutes, and all
6 actions taken thereunder, are hereby validated, ratified, and
7 continued in full force and effect as if adopted under the authority
8 of Sections 868.1 et seq. of Title 19 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
9 until amended, revised, or replaced by appropriate official action
10 taken in accordance with such sections.
11 SECTION 4. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
12 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
13 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
14 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
